data.description: Nestled in the heart of midtown Tucson, this 1948 Santa Fe Style Home offers a unique blend of Tucson charm, privacy and convenience. Featuring a split three bedroom floorplan, two bathrooms, a sparkling pool, a cozy fireplace, a spacious laundry room/utility room, and a large lot perfect for a guest house or lush garden. The primary suite also features a private entrance, offering ideal guest quarters.   The exterior of the home also has a small pond, three car carport, and space for RV Parking. Let your imagination run wild with landscaping and outdoor living possibilities.  Its unique blend of traditional style, fantastic location, potential for expansion, and modern amenities create a remarkable property that is both a comfortable sanctuary and a canvas for your future.
